# Numen UI Design Track ÔÇö rules for this worktree

This worktree (`virtuna-ui-restrained`, branch `design/ui-restrained`) is the **UI design track** ÔÇö
the restrained-accent rebrand (de-Claude). It runs in PARALLEL with an engine/backend rework in a
separate worktree (`virtuna-engine-rework`, branch `rework/engine-core`). Stay in your lane to avoid
conflicts. The prior design batch (`design/ui-system`) is already merged to `main` ÔÇö branch off
`main`, not off the old branch.

## 1. Design system ÔÇö trust ONE source
- The **only** authoritative design references are `src/app/globals.css` (the `@theme` token
  block) and `docs/DESIGN-SYSTEM.md`. Read `docs/DESIGN-SYSTEM.md` before any visual work.
- **IGNORE these ÔÇö they are STALE** (they describe the retired Raycast/coral/glass system):
  `CLAUDE.md` "Raycast Design Language Rules" section, `BRAND-BIBLE.md`, `docs/tokens.md`,
  `docs/components.md`, `docs/design-specs.json`, `docs/usage-guidelines.md`,
  `docs/motion-guidelines.md`, `docs/brand/`.
- Current system = **flat-warm charcoal + cream text + MONOCHROME-by-default (accent near-zero) + matte**:
  - bg `#262624` (`--color-background`), cream text `#ece7de` (`--cream-primary`) ÔÇö **never `#fff`**
  - accent = **signal red `#e23b2d`** (`--color-accent`), the logo mark ÔÇö **terracotta `#d97757` is RETIRED** (it read too close to Claude). Never `#FF7F50`.
  - **ACCENT DOSAGE IS LOCKED ÔÇö MONOCHROME BY DEFAULT, accent used REALLY sparingly, if at all.** A screen with ZERO accent is the norm, not a failure. Every accent use must be justified; aim for at most ONE accent element per view, often zero. The ONLY sanctioned uses: the single live presence/liveness dot, the lit constellation/SIM node, the brand mark. FORBIDDEN everywhere else ÔÇö primary buttons, icon buttons, skill pills, chevrons, placeholders, tabs, toggles, links, borders, charts, badges, large fills, hover states, and anything "to make it pop." Read "Accent dosage (LOCKED)" in `docs/DESIGN-SYSTEM.md` before touching color.
  - **Primary actions are NEUTRAL cream** ÔÇö use `--color-action` / `--color-action-foreground`, NOT the accent. (Composer send = cream button, dark glyph.)
  - accent-as-text on dark Ôćĺ `--color-accent-text` (`#ef6e62`); soft tint bg Ôćĺ `--color-accent-soft`. Solid-red fill glyph Ôćĺ `--color-accent-foreground` (cream).
  - `--color-accent` (brand red) Ôëá `--color-error` (data/destructive red). Never conflate.
  - borders 6% (`rgba(255,255,255,0.06)`), hover 10%
  - **matte only**: no glass gradients, no glow, no white inset-shine. Flat + border + (rarely) `--shadow-float`.
  - Inter for all chrome; serif (`--font-serif`, Newsreader; Fraunces candidate) **only** for voice-moments (greeting/hero).
  - radius 4/6/8/12/16/20/24 ÔÇö cards 12, inputs/buttons 8.
  - **Identity is carried by the constellation/SIM motif + serif voice + copy**, since color is now quiet. Invest there.
- **Always consume tokens, never hardcode hex.** No `#FF7F50`, `#07080a`, `#18191a`, `#fff`, no raw `#d97757`/`#e23b2d` in components.
- Keep `src/components/reading/__tests__/reskin-matte.test.ts` GREEN (guards against coral/glass).

## 2. File ownership ÔÇö DO NOT cross
- Ôťů **You own:** `src/components/**`, page-level styling/layout in `src/app/(app)/**` (NON-api),
  `src/app/globals.css`, design tokens, `src/types/design-tokens.ts`.
- ÔŤö **Do NOT touch (engine track owns these):** `src/lib/**`, `src/app/api/**`, runners,
  engine, `supabase/**`, prompt/KC files. If a UI change seems to need a backend change,
  STOP and flag it ÔÇö don't edit backend here.

## 3. Coupled surfaces ÔÇö visual-only, don't change contracts
`AudienceLens`, the composer, and the thread skill-cards are being reworked on the engine side
(their data shape/props may change). For these you MAY restyle/relayout, but **do NOT change the
props/data contracts** they consume or the block schemas. Structural changes to these wait for
the engine rework ÔÇö coordinate first.

### 3a. ÔŤö Engine-rework HOLD list ÔÇö do NOT edit (guaranteed merge conflict)
`rework/engine-core` (worktree `~/virtuna-engine-rework`) is 8 commits ahead of main, NOT yet
merged, and is actively rewriting these UI-lane files. Editing them here will conflict:
- `src/components/audience/calibration-flow.tsx`
- `src/components/audience/audience-reveal.tsx`
Leave both untouched until that branch lands on main. Everything else in `src/components/**` and
